1
00:00:00,375 --> 00:00:04,875
Interviewer: While you were in the detention room, did any of you develop a chronic illness

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,625
Or did someone get scabies or a skin disease

3
00:00:10,791 --> 00:00:17,041
Such that he needed special medical care, or to be moved to another place?

4
00:00:17,208 --> 00:00:20,666
No, that did not happen, but one day

5
00:00:20,750 --> 00:00:24,583
As I heard, someone became very ill and they transferred him to the hospital

6
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:29,208
Interviewer: Did they take him to the hospital, or did a doctor come to you?

7
00:00:29,291 --> 00:00:30,833
No, to the hospital, no doctor came to us

8
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:32,333
Interviewer: No doctor came to you?

9
00:00:32,416 --> 00:00:36,000
The one whose condition was critical from the start would be transferred to the hospital, as I heard

10
00:00:36,708 --> 00:00:38,833
Interviewer: Was the one taken to the hospital under guard?

11
00:00:39,083 --> 00:00:42,500
We didn’t know if they took him to the hospital or to the clinic

12
00:00:42,791 --> 00:00:44,833
We only knew they moved him to another place

13
00:00:45,125 --> 00:00:51,000
Interviewer: If you or one of the prisoners had a headache or his blood pressure rose

14
00:00:51,125 --> 00:00:54,000
Or got the flu or similar illnesses

15
00:00:54,416 --> 00:01:00,041
Would a doctor or a nurse come to provide you with treatment and health care?

16
00:01:00,291 --> 00:01:03,500
No, no, that didn’t happen with us, and no one asked us

17
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,291
Interviewer: Didn’t you ever ask a jailer for treatment?

18
00:01:07,666 --> 00:01:11,250
No, no, but one day someone was talking and he said

19
00:01:11,916 --> 00:01:13,041
And he had been in the prison before me

20
00:01:13,750 --> 00:01:20,083
He said—There was a person with us, his condition was critical, he got very sick, and he had a chronic illness

21
00:01:20,208 --> 00:01:22,791
He had epilepsy—a nerve disorder—I think, or something like that

22
00:01:22,875 --> 00:01:26,041
He fell ill suddenly, and they came, took him, and transferred him to the hospital

23
00:01:26,250 --> 00:01:28,125
Interviewer: Did they bring him back? Witness: Yes, they brought him back

24
00:01:28,708 --> 00:01:31,875
They brought him the next day—they took him to the hospital or somewhere else, I don’t know

25
00:01:33,208 --> 00:01:34,833
To the hospital or somewhere else, I don’t know
